Key Match Events: Marcus Semien's line single scored the game-winning run in the ninth inning
Leody Taveras hit a solo home run in the seventh inning to tie the game at 5-5
Miscellaneous Highlights: The defending World Series champion Rangers, who were eliminated from postseason contention on Friday, improved to 7-61 when trailing after six innings
Others: Andrew Heaney started for the Rangers and allowed four earned runs on seven hits with four strikeouts and a walk in 5 2/3 innings
Bryce Miller will start for the Mariners in their next game against the Astros, while Nathan Eovaldi will start for the Rangers against the Athletics
